oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Trench silo for cattle feed
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Clement, William L., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Trench silo which has been used for two years. Silo is used to provide adequate feed for dairy and beef cattle on a small farm. Silo is covered with sheet of plastic separating six inches of sawdust on top. Located twelve miles southeast of Woodbury.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
